DATA SOURCES ACKNOWLEDGMENT:

This project uses publicly available data from multiple federal agencies with required attributions:

NAEP Data: National Center for Education Statistics, Institute of Education Sciences, 
U.S. Department of Education, National Assessment of Educational Progress (NAEP)

IDEA Data: U.S. Department of Education, Office of Special Education Programs, 
Individuals with Disabilities Education Act (IDEA) Section 618 Data Products

Census Data: U.S. Census Bureau, Annual Survey of School System Finances (F-33)

OCR Data: U.S. Department of Education, Office for Civil Rights, 
Civil Rights Data Collection (CRDC)

ACKNOWLEDGMENT: This research uses data made available by the National Center for 
Education Statistics (NAEP), the Office of Special Education Programs (IDEA data), 
the U.S. Census Bureau (education finance data), and the Office for Civil Rights 
(civil rights data). The conclusions drawn from these data are solely those of the 
author(s) and do not necessarily represent the views or positions of the U.S. 
Department of Education, U.S. Census Bureau, or any other federal agency.

All data usage complies with federal terms of service and citation requirements.